<h1>Control Loops</h1>
<p>Sometimes you may need to do a certain task many times. Loops allow you to control iterative tasks.</p>
<h2><code>for</code></h2>
<img class='wide' src='images/syntax_anatomy/for.svg' onerror="this.src='images/syntax_anatomy/for.png'" />
<p>Use the <code>for</code> loop to do something a certain number of times. This loop allows you to loop using a variable you make (usually <code>i, j</code> or <code>k</code>). You do this in the following steps:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create and initialize the variable to count with</li>
<li>Set a condition to continue looping</li>
<li>Update the variable at each loop</li></ul>
<p>This may seem like a lot but it's almost always like this:
</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">
// Read an entire book
for (int i = 0 ; i < pagesInBook ; i++){
	readPage(i);
}
</pre>

<h2>enhanced <code>for</code></h2>
<img class='wide' src='images/syntax_anatomy/for_enhanced.svg' onerror="this.src='images/syntax_anatomy/for_enhanced.png'" />
<p>Use the enhanced <code>for</code> loop as a convenient way to go through each entry in collection.</p>
<pre class="prettyprint">
// Shooting arrows
for (Arrow currentArrow : allArrows){
	shoot(currentArrow);
}
</pre>

<h2><code>while</code></h2>
<img src='images/syntax_anatomy/while.svg' onerror="this.src='images/syntax_anatomy/while.png'" />
<p>Use the <code>while</code> loop to keep looping as long as the condition is met.<br/> <strong>*Be careful</strong> as it it very common to accidentally create an infinite loop with no end.</p>
<pre class="prettyprint">
// Pass out a deck of cards
while (deckContainsCards){
	passOutAnotherCard();
}
</pre>

<h2><code>do while</code></h2>
<img src='images/syntax_anatomy/do_while.svg' onerror="this.src='images/syntax_anatomy/do_while.png'" />
<p>Use the <code>do while</code> loop much like the <code>while</code> loop. The only difference is this loop is always done at least once.<br/> <strong>*Be careful</strong> as it it very common to accidentally create an infinite loop with no end.</p>
<pre class="prettyprint">
// Stuffing a pillow
do{
	addStuffing();
}while (notEnoughStuffing);
</pre>

</body>
